Krama

1. Clone the repository and change to the project directory

        ```sh
        git clone https://github.com/mohanrajvijayan2410/krama.git
        cd krama
        ```

        Note: You can download the zip file from the repository and extract it too. Change the current directory to the extracted directory

2. Create a virtual enviroment and activate it.
        ```sh
        python -m venv kramaenv

        kramaenv\Scripts\activate
        ```

3. Install the neccessary modules.

    
            pip install -r requirements.txt
        

5. Change directory to your desired folder and run the app.py using "python app.py"

    ```sh
    cd <sub_folder> 
    ```

    Replace `<sub_folder>` with one of the following options:
    - Arthakrama
    - Pathakrama
    - Pravarittikrama
    - Shrutikrama

    6. Kindly refer the the individual README files within each folder for further instructions
    

